<h1>3 easy steps to integrate AcceptTheTerms</h1>

<h2>1. Create EULA in your account</h2>
<p>You can create as many parts as you want. And use different parts on different pages.</p>
<p>You should correctly specify your website domain to allow the service working properly.</p>

<h2>2. Install code to your site</h2>

<button class="btn btn-info js-show-instructions">Show me instructions</button>

<pre class="js-hidden hidden inc-code">
  <code class="html">
    <%= "<script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"http://accepttheterms.ivanthecrazy.koding.io/eula.js\"></script>" %>
  </code>
</pre>

<h2>3. Integrate our code with your site logic</h2>
<pre>
  <code class="js">
    $(document).ready(function () {
      // You can specify your user_id to allow service store it for future use
      // Otherwise, user_id will be generated by service
      var user_id = '';

      // Initialize service
      // styles can be obtained via customization section or can be empty for default styles

      var eula = new Eula(user_id, styles);

      // Set window show points
      // 'test' is license agreement part code
      eula.show('test', {
        // Callback on accept license agreement part
        accept: function () {
          alert('accepted!');
        },

        // Callback on decline license agreement part
        decline: function () {
          alert('declined!');
        },

        // Callback on simple closed window
        hide: function () {
          alert('just close the window');
        }
      });

      // Also you can check that current user has previously accepted some parts of EULA
      // 'INSTRUCTION' is license agreement part code
      // function is the callback to be called when all data recieved from our server
      eula.isAccepted('INSTRUCTIONS', function (accepted) {
        if (accepted) {
          ufoStart();
        }
      });
    });"
  </code>
</pre>

<h2>Job is done!</h2>
<p>Now your site has great interactive EULA solution. And you can view statistics on your EULAs list.</p>

